   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">First you use Gogor to go on the offensive and try to limit the players creatures.  this guves you time to keep drawing cards at the end of your turn and with the nice supply of burrowed creatures you are able to keep your guys alive.  use Radget to gain impacts wich go good as a combo with ormagon and crystal arboll&#39;s to totally kill a magi in one turn.  then if you haven&#39;t killed them already you can move to the attack of the korrits with ULK.  with 9 korrits, you should be able to have almost all of them by the time Ulk comes out and plays, plus all the bounuses gained with korrits then you should be able to unleash a fury of korrits to attack, either in packs or alone, your choice.   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
